WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.420 --> 00:00:08.180
In British Columbia students are expected to meet

00:00:08.360 --> 00:00:11.920
certain criteria in order to meet Ministry of Education requirements.

00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:16.060
Here at Bodwell high school, we work closely with students

00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:18.780
To help them follow through with their graduation plan

00:00:19.180 --> 00:00:21.320
Take a look at this.

00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:25.860
This graduation plan can be found on our website.

00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:50.700
There are six main components to our graduation program,

00:00:50.980 --> 00:00:52.540
the first being "communication".

00:00:52.540 --> 00:00:54.879
We have relevant up-to-date communication

00:00:54.880 --> 00:00:58.920
between staff and students, which is imperative for student success.

00:00:58.920 --> 00:01:04.290
We use email personalized notifications, one-on-one and  group meetings, online grading program

00:01:04.290 --> 00:01:08.400
"my blueprint" software, daily announcements, and bulletin boards

00:01:08.400 --> 00:01:11.540
to communicate essential information to our students

00:01:12.080 --> 00:01:15.240
The second component is "graduation requirements".

00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:19.240
Our counselors individually explore.graduation requirements with students.

00:01:19.240 --> 00:01:22.960
They ensure that students have completed the 80 credits needed

00:01:23.160 --> 00:01:25.780
to graduate with a BC high school diploma.

00:01:25.780 --> 00:01:29.940
We offer a wide variety of grade 10, 11, and 12 courses

00:01:29.940 --> 00:01:34.020
including Advanced Placement calculus, Studio Art, Physics, and Mandarin.

00:01:34.600 --> 00:01:39.100
Over 30 after-school clubs and 40 Saturday enrichment courses

00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:43.680
are offered to help students supplement their learning and enrich their post-secondary applications.

00:01:43.740 --> 00:01:49.040
The third component is "provincial exams". The previous provincial exams are being replaced

00:01:49.040 --> 00:01:52.740
by two provincial assessments -  literacy and numeracy.

00:01:52.740 --> 00:01:55.560
They are offered in January, June, and August of each year.

00:01:55.900 --> 00:01:57.880
In addition to classroom instruction,

00:01:57.890 --> 00:02:01.419
students will be given numerous opportunities to prepare for those two assessments

00:02:01.850 --> 00:02:05.979
via academic clubs and extra practice sessions that are offered after school.

00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:10.520
The fourth component is "English proficiency".

00:02:10.640 --> 00:02:13.760
We assist students by offering IELTS enrichment courses

00:02:13.760 --> 00:02:18.960
The fifth "career life connections and career life education".

00:02:18.960 --> 00:02:23.320
Before students graduate students they must complete two academic courses:

00:02:23.320 --> 00:02:25.840
career life connections and career life education.

00:02:26.020 --> 00:02:29.740
that are designed to help students prepare to be lifelong learners

00:02:29.740 --> 00:02:31.720
and to find a balance between school and personal life.

00:02:32.040 --> 00:02:35.320
These are components that are essential to balanced physical and mental health.

00:02:36.160 --> 00:02:39.140
Students will be expected to do at least 30 hours

00:02:39.140 --> 00:02:43.160
of volunteer experience and successfully produce a capstone project.

00:02:43.160 --> 00:02:46.980
The sixth component is the post-secondary plan.

00:02:46.980 --> 00:02:51.739
we offer a rich support program for post-secondary applications.

00:02:51.739 --> 00:02:55.809
When a student graduates from Bodwell high school they can feel confident

00:02:55.809 --> 00:02:58.280
they have received the individualized support

00:02:58.400 --> 00:03:00.820
for their post-secondary endeavours

